data.description:
Your task is to hijack a different JVM with a given PID and extract a security code as a String.

The class which holds the security code looks like this:

```java
public class Burglary$Target {

	private static String securityCode;
}
```

In the validation text cases you need to pass 3 times in a row.

Inspired by <a href="https://www.codewars.com/users/jcsahnwaldt">jcsahnwaldt</a>'s <a href="https://www.codewars.com/kata/5510caecaacf801f820002ac">Hack-22</a> and many other fun Katas on Codewars. If you like hacking challenges as much as i do check out this <a href="https://www.codewars.com/collections/hacking">Collection</a>.

<b>Hint:</b> Take a look at the <a href="https://bytebuddy.net/">ByteBuddy</a> library which is available in the Kata environment.
